<div class="la-wrapper la-wrapper--about">
  <div class="app-shell">
    <main class="la-main" role="main">

      <section id="faq-hero" class="la-section">
        <div class="la-section-header" style="display: block; text-align: center;">
          <span class="la-section-eyebrow-badge">{{t "HELP" key="faq_eyebrow"}} <span class="la-about-hero-brand">Lingo</span><span class="la-about-hero-brand la-about-hero-brand--italic">Linq</span></span>
          <div class="la-hero-title-wrap">
            <h1 class="la-hero-title">{{t "Frequently Asked " key="faq_title_prefix"}}<span class="hero-gradient">{{t "Questions" key="faq_title_highlight"}}</span></h1>
          </div>
          <hr class="la-about-hero-separator" aria-hidden="true">
          <p class="la-pricing-hero-subtitle">{{t "Short answers to common questions about using LingoLinq." key="faq_page_subtitle"}}</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="faq-items" class="la-section">
        <div class="la-section-header">
          <span class="la-section-eyebrow-badge">{{t "FAQ" key="faq_subsection_faq_eyebrow"}}</span>
          <h2 class="la-section-title">{{t "Common " key="faq_subsection_faq_title_1"}}<em>{{t "questions" key="faq_subsection_faq_title_2"}}</em></h2>
          <hr class="la-about-hero-separator" aria-hidden="true">
        </div>
        <div class="la-feature-grid">
          <article class="la-feature-card la-feature-card--faq">
            <div class="la-feature-icon la-feature-icon--teal" aria-hidden="true">✨</div>
            <h3 class="la-faq-article__title" id="faq-article-ai-boards-heading">{{t "What are some interesting and engaging speech boards I can create using AI board generation?" key="faq_ai_boards_q"}}</h3>
            {{#unless this.articleAiBoardsExpanded}}
              <button type="button" class="la-faq-read-toggle" {{action "toggleArticleAiBoards"}} aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-article-ai-boards-body">{{t "Read more..." key="faq_read_more"}}</button>
            {{/unless}}
            {{#if this.articleAiBoardsExpanded}}
              <div id="faq-article-ai-boards-body" class="la-faq-article-body" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-article-ai-boards-heading">
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AI board generation turns a short description into a starter layout you can edit—buttons, groups, and paths you refine like any other board. The most engaging boards are tied to real life: a specific routine, place, person, or goal, with vocabulary the communicator will actually want to use that week." key="faq_ai_boards_p1"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Try prompting for situations, not just categories. Instead of only \"food words,\" describe \"ordering lunch in the cafeteria\" or \"choosing a snack after school.\" Mix core words (want, help, more, stop) with fringe words for that moment (allergy, spicy, debit card, teammate). That balance keeps boards useful in conversation, not just as a static word list." key="faq_ai_boards_p2"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Ideas that work well in classrooms and clinics:" key="faq_ai_boards_list_intro"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list">
                  <li>{{t "Daily living: morning routine, chores, homework, bedtime—each with a small set of predictable phrases." key="faq_ai_boards_li_1"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Social participation: playground games, club meetings, video calls with family, small talk with neighbors." key="faq_ai_boards_li_2"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Community access: grocery store, restaurant, pharmacy, library—scripts for questions, choices, and problem-solving." key="faq_ai_boards_li_3"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Learning: science vocabulary for a unit, math talk (estimate, compare, prove), field trip safety and participation." key="faq_ai_boards_li_4"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Play and hobbies: rules and turns for favorite games, sports cheers, art or music lesson requests." key="faq_ai_boards_li_5"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Regulation and health: calming choices, pain or comfort scale, explaining symptoms, allergy and medication phrases." key="faq_ai_boards_li_6"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "After generation, edit ruthlessly: rename buttons in the communicator's voice, swap symbols so they read quickly, and link back to a stable home or backup board. Start with one situation that matters this month, then duplicate and adapt once it feels comfortable." key="faq_ai_boards_p3"}}</p>
              </div>
              <button type="button" class="la-faq-read-toggle la-faq-read-toggle--after" {{action "toggleArticleAiBoards"}} aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-article-ai-boards-body">{{t "Read less" key="faq_read_less"}}</button>
            {{/if}}
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="faq-questions" class="la-section">
        <div class="la-section-header">
          <span class="la-section-eyebrow-badge">{{t "Articles" key="faq_section_articles"}}</span>
          <h2 class="la-section-title">{{t "Tips and " key="faq_section_title_1"}}<em>{{t "how-tos" key="faq_section_title_2"}}</em></h2>
          <hr class="la-about-hero-separator" aria-hidden="true">
        </div>
        <div class="la-feature-grid">
          <article class="la-feature-card la-feature-card--faq">
            <div class="la-feature-icon la-feature-icon--navy" aria-hidden="true">💬</div>
            <h3 class="la-faq-article__title" id="faq-article-aac-heading">{{t "What Is AAC? (A Simple Guide for Parents & Caregivers)" key="faq_aac_q"}}</h3>
            {{#unless this.articleAacGuideExpanded}}
              <button type="button" class="la-faq-read-toggle" {{action "toggleArticleAacGuide"}} aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-article-aac-body">{{t "Read more..." key="faq_read_more"}}</button>
            {{/unless}}
            {{#if this.articleAacGuideExpanded}}
              <div id="faq-article-aac-body" class="la-faq-article-body" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-article-aac-heading">
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "If your child—or someone you care for—has difficulty speaking, you may have heard the term AAC. It can feel overwhelming at first, but AAC is simply about helping people communicate in the way that works best for them." key="faq_aac_intro_p1"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "This guide will walk you through what AAC means, who it’s for, the different types available, and how tools like LingoLinq fit into the picture." key="faq_aac_intro_p2"}}</p>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "What Does AAC Stand For?" key="faq_aac_sub_what_stand"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC stands for Augmentative and Alternative Communication." key="faq_aac_stand_for_line"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Augmentative = adding to speech" key="faq_aac_def_augmentative_line"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Alternative = replacing speech" key="faq_aac_def_alternative_line"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text la-faq-lead">{{t "In simple terms:" key="faq_aac_simple_terms_lead"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC includes any method of communication that helps someone express themselves if speaking is difficult or not possible." key="faq_aac_simple_body"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC is not just for people who “can’t talk”—it’s for anyone who needs support communicating more effectively." key="faq_aac_not_just"}}</p>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "Who Is AAC For?" key="faq_aac_sub_who"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC is used by people of all ages, from young children to adults. It can support individuals with:" key="faq_aac_who_intro"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list">
                  <li>{{t "Autism" key="faq_aac_who_li_autism"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Cerebral palsy" key="faq_aac_who_li_cp"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Down syndrome" key="faq_aac_who_li_down"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Apraxia of speech" key="faq_aac_who_li_apraxia"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Stroke or brain injury" key="faq_aac_who_li_stroke"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "ALS or other degenerative conditions" key="faq_aac_who_li_als"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Temporary speech loss (injury, surgery, etc.)" key="faq_aac_who_li_temp"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Some people use AAC short-term, while others rely on it throughout their lives." key="faq_aac_who_duration"}}</p>
                <aside class="la-faq-callout" aria-label={{t "Important to know" key="faq_aac_important_label"}}>
                  <p class="la-faq-callout__title">{{t "Important to know:" key="faq_aac_important_label_colon"}}</p>
                  <p class="la-faq-callout__text">{{t "Using AAC does not stop someone from learning to speak. In many cases, it actually supports and improves speech development." key="faq_aac_important_body"}}</p>
                </aside>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "Types of AAC" key="faq_aac_sub_types"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC can be broken into two main categories:" key="faq_aac_types_intro"}}</p>

                <div class="la-faq-type-block">
                  <h5 class="la-faq-type-block__title">{{t "1. No-Tech / Low-Tech AAC" key="faq_aac_sub_low_tech"}}</h5>
                  <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "These do not require electronics." key="faq_aac_low_tech_desc"}}</p>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Examples:" key="faq_aac_examples_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Gestures (pointing, nodding)" key="faq_aac_low_ex_gestures"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Sign language" key="faq_aac_low_ex_sign"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Picture boards" key="faq_aac_low_ex_pictures"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Printed communication books" key="faq_aac_low_ex_books"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Pros:" key="faq_aac_pros_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Simple and reliable" key="faq_aac_low_pro_1"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "No batteries or setup" key="faq_aac_low_pro_2"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Cons:" key="faq_aac_cons_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Limited vocabulary" key="faq_aac_low_con_1"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Harder to adapt quickly" key="faq_aac_low_con_2"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="la-faq-type-block la-faq-type-block--follow">
                  <h5 class="la-faq-type-block__title">{{t "2. High-Tech AAC" key="faq_aac_sub_high_tech"}}</h5>
                  <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "These are electronic tools or apps that help people communicate." key="faq_aac_high_tech_desc"}}</p>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Examples:" key="faq_aac_examples_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Speech-generating devices (SGDs)" key="faq_aac_high_ex_sgd"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Tablet-based AAC apps" key="faq_aac_high_ex_tablet"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Eye-tracking or gaze-based systems" key="faq_aac_high_ex_gaze"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Pros:" key="faq_aac_pros_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Larger vocabulary" key="faq_aac_high_pro_1"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Can generate speech" key="faq_aac_high_pro_2"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "Highly customizable" key="faq_aac_high_pro_3"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Cons:" key="faq_aac_cons_label"}}</p>
                  <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                    <li>{{t "Requires setup and learning" key="faq_aac_high_con_1"}}</li>
                    <li>{{t "May be more expensive" key="faq_aac_high_con_2"}}</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "How AAC Actually Works" key="faq_aac_sub_how_works"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Most AAC systems are built around a communication board—a layout of buttons, symbols, or words." key="faq_aac_how_p1"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "A user might:" key="faq_aac_user_might_label"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Tap a button" key="faq_aac_user_li_tap"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Select a picture" key="faq_aac_user_li_picture"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Use their eyes (gaze tracking)" key="faq_aac_user_li_gaze"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "The system then:" key="faq_aac_system_then_label"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Speaks the word or phrase" key="faq_aac_system_li_speak"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Builds a sentence" key="faq_aac_system_li_sentence"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Stores communication history" key="faq_aac_system_li_history"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Over time, users learn where words are located and how to navigate quickly—just like typing on a keyboard." key="faq_aac_how_p2"}}</p>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "Where LingoLinq Fits In" key="faq_aac_sub_lingolinq"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "LingoLinq is part of the next generation of AAC tools—focused not just on communication, but on improving how communication happens." key="faq_aac_ll_intro"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "What makes it different?" key="faq_aac_ll_diff_q"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "Most AAC tools focus on:" key="faq_aac_ll_most_focus"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "What words are selected" key="faq_aac_ll_most_li"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "LingoLinq also focuses on:" key="faq_aac_ll_also_focus"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "How users interact with the board" key="faq_aac_ll_also_li"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "This includes:" key="faq_aac_ll_includes_label"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Where users tap" key="faq_aac_ll_inc_tap"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "How long it takes to find a word" key="faq_aac_ll_inc_time"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Areas that are hard to reach" key="faq_aac_ll_inc_reach"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Patterns in navigation" key="faq_aac_ll_inc_patterns"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "Why that matters:" key="faq_aac_ll_why_label"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "For caregivers, therapists, and educators, this can help answer questions like:" key="faq_aac_ll_why_intro"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Is the board layout working well?" key="faq_aac_ll_q_layout"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Which buttons are confusing or hard to find?" key="faq_aac_ll_q_buttons"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Where is the user struggling?" key="faq_aac_ll_q_struggling"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "This kind of insight can lead to:" key="faq_aac_ll_insight_lead"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "Better board design" key="faq_aac_ll_out_design"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Faster communication" key="faq_aac_ll_out_faster"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "More independence for the user" key="faq_aac_ll_out_independence"}}</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "The Bigger Picture" key="faq_aac_sub_bigger"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "AAC is not just about tools—it’s about giving people a voice." key="faq_aac_bigger_p1"}}</p>
                <p class="la-faq-inline-label">{{t "The right AAC system can:" key="faq_aac_bigger_can_label"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list">
                  <li>{{t "Reduce frustration" key="faq_aac_bigger_li_frustration"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Increase independence" key="faq_aac_bigger_li_independence"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Improve social connection" key="faq_aac_bigger_li_social"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Support learning and development" key="faq_aac_bigger_li_learning"}}</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "And as technology evolves, AAC is becoming:" key="faq_aac_future_intro"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list la-faq-list--tight">
                  <li>{{t "More personalized" key="faq_aac_future_li_1"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "More adaptive" key="faq_aac_future_li_2"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "More intelligent" key="faq_aac_future_li_3"}}</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="la-faq-subhead">{{t "Final Thoughts" key="faq_aac_sub_final"}}</h4>
                <p class="la-faq-card__text">{{t "If you’re just starting your AAC journey, remember:" key="faq_aac_final_intro"}}</p>
                <ul class="la-faq-list">
                  <li>{{t "There is no “one-size-fits-all” solution" key="faq_aac_final_li_1"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "It’s okay to try different approaches" key="faq_aac_final_li_2"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "Progress takes time—but it’s meaningful" key="faq_aac_final_li_3"}}</li>
                  <li>{{t "The goal isn’t perfection—it’s communication" key="faq_aac_final_li_4"}}</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <button type="button" class="la-faq-read-toggle la-faq-read-toggle--after" {{action "toggleArticleAacGuide"}} aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-article-aac-body">{{t "Read less" key="faq_read_less"}}</button>
            {{/if}}
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="la-cta-section">
        <div class="la-cta-inner">
          <span class="la-section-eyebrow-badge">{{t "Still need help?" key="faq_cta_eyebrow"}}</span>
          <p class="la-cta-description">{{t "Report a problem, send feedback, or reach the team from the support page." key="faq_cta_body"}}</p>
          <div class="la-cta-buttons">
            <LinkTo @route="support" class="la-btn la-btn--primary">{{t "Go to Support" key="faq_cta_support"}}</LinkTo>
            <LinkTo @route="contact" class="la-btn la-btn--ghost">{{t "Contact Us" key="contact_us"}}</LinkTo>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</div>
